  "prompt": "How do I search if any of my friends and relatives are here on Quora?",
  "response": "To search for friends and relatives on Quora, follow these steps:\n\n1. Log in to your Quora account.\n\n2. Click on the search bar at the top of the page.\n\n3. Type in the name of the person you're looking for. If you know their username, you can enter that as well.\n\n4. Press Enter or click on the magnifying glass icon to initiate the search.\n\n5. Quora will display a list of results that match the name you entered. You can filter the results by selecting \"People\" from the tabs at the top of the search results page.\n\n6. If you see the person you're looking for in the search results, click on their name to visit their profile.\n\n7. If you don't find the person you're looking for, try searching for variations of their name or using any other information you know about them, such as their profession or location.\n\nAdditionally, you can invite friends and relatives to join Quora if they're not already members. To do this:\n\n1. Click on your profile picture in the top right corner of the page, then select \"Settings\" from the dropdown menu.\n\n2. In the left sidebar, click on \"Invite Friends.\"\n\n3. You can invite friends via email, or by sharing a link on social media platforms like Facebook or Twitter.\n\nRemember to respect the privacy of others and only connect with people you know personally or have a legitimate reason to contact.",
